untouched accounts, although the README suggests prioritizing untouched first.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating spec clarity and rotation logic**\\n\\nI’m considering whether the spec should mention preserving exact code behavior, since it talks about selection heuristic divergence and stable contracts. But maybe that’s not currently visible to the user. I should verify the rotation logic: if a quota or rate-limit error occurs before any streamed output, it should trigger an account cooldown, rotation, and retry, which makes sense. Also, if any output is forwarded, the stream shouldn't silently rotate but should forward the error and end instead. Finally, failed accounts should be marked exhausted until the reset time, or a fallback cooldown if the reset time isn't known.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking the codebase**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether to align against the codebase that includes `.agents/sources/pi-multicodex/`. It wasn't specifically requested, so I could ignore it. However, since the spec mentions it, I might need to check if that source exists. Honestly, it might not be absolutely necessary, but hey, it could be quick to just list it and see what's there! Let’s see what I can find!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_K50WMZXW60JuuDJ3JX4ZykNE|fc_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de0352fe288199a470fcab3e36b861","name":"ls","arguments":{"path":".agents/sources","limit":100},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\".agents/sources\",\"limit\":100}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6DOykCLDKjyu3PocnNusNnZE|fc_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de0352fe3c8199b7f0fc4fc7eecd76","name":"ls","arguments":{"path":".agents/sources/pi-multicodex","limit":100},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\".agents/sources/pi-multicodex\",\"limit\":100}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":2394,"output":1528,"cacheRead":33664,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37586,"cost":{"input":0.005985000000000001,"output":0.02292,"cacheRead":0.