n refresh deduplication parity, but the current code doesn’t reflect that. This lack of alignment could be misleading, so we need to address it critically.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering testing strategies**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the future of our testing strategy. It seems the current test suite is incomplete since it’s focused in the root. The specs suggest splitting tests by module and maintaining a compatibility smoke suite, which sounds good. However, the acceptance criteria don't clearly state the smoke tests count or adapter tests for warnings on unavailable providers. I also see some missing acceptance criteria for storage migration and public export compatibility, which is important to address.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating code improvements**\\n\\nI’m noticing that the current code has a warning handler and manual selection but lacks eventing. This seems like an important improvement to consider, possibly making it optional to avoid unnecessary complexity in the event system. \\n\\nI should check `progress.md` for notes and consider adding a review section later.\\n\\nI also need to determine if there are critical issues, maybe around three critical and five important. I should provide specific patch suggestions, perhaps using structured bullet lists and section citations.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering grep for citations**\\n\\nI’m thinking it might be better to use grep to search for specific headings or phrases in the specifications as anchors. While I can't use line numbers directly, I could utilize grep for notable phrases from the spec for citations. Since line numbers aren't available, maybe I can use grep with literal phrases instead. This could help in constructing clearer references to relevant sections without making it overly complicated.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_aiXNk39Of3SlQWfiapHvx49O|fc_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de038f37408199af1d6ca09c1f15ac","name":"grep","arguments":{"path":".agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md","pattern":"Token refresh|Current repo state|Public interfaces|Storage and migration strategy|Phase 4|Definition of done|multicodex-use|multicodex-switch|StorageData|TokenRefresher|onStateChange","literal":true,"context":2,"limit":200},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\".agents/tasks/refactor-agnostic/spec.md\",\"pattern\":\"Token refresh|Current repo state|Public interfaces|Storage and migration strategy|Phase 4|Definition of done|multicodex-use|multicodex-switch|StorageData|TokenRefresher|onStateChange\",\"literal\":true,\"context\":2,\"limit\":200}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":338,"output":2094,"cacheRead":37760,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40192,"cost":{"input":0.000845,"output":0.03141,"cacheRead":0.009439999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.041694999999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776157531428,"responseId":"resp_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de035c2c2c8199ae779bc1018cb890"}}
