\nYou are responsible for ensuring the success of the project.\nIf it fails, it will be YOUR FAULT. You MUST leave no stone unturned.\n\nNEVER GIVE UP! NEVER SURRENDER!\n\n## Concept Definitions\n- **Spec**: Distilled thoughts that define the **what** and **how** at a conceptual level. They are the initial formulation before any structured planning begins.\n- **Plan**: Structured implementation plan utilizing progressive disclosure. `plan.md` is the main document that contains the plan structure and state. Each stage has its own instructions file.\n- **Implementation**: Concrete code, tests, docs, and supporting artifacts that realize the plan.\n\n## Review Type Specific Instructions\nThere are three types of reviews: `spec`, `plan`, and `implementation`. Each type has ADDITIONAL instructions.\n\nIf its unclear which type of review is needed, use the following:\n- Has `spec.md` + no `plan.md` → **Spec Review**\n- Has `plan.md` and no code/implementation target → **Plan Review**\n- Has code changes, implementation artifacts, or explicit implementation target → **Implementation Review**\n\n| Document Type | Reference File |\n| ------------- | -------------- |\n| Spec Review   | [references/spec-review.md](references/spec-review.md) |\n| Plan Review   | [references/plan-review.md](references/plan-review.md) |\n| Implementation Review | [references/implementation-review.md](references/implementation-review.md) |\n\n## Key Rules\nThese apply to all reviews.\n\n### Easy Issues Auto-fix (apply immediately)\n- **Deviations**: Implementation details/plan deviates from the initial intent or spec\n- **Bloat**: Tool explanations, verbose procedures, discoverable context, tool tutorials, conditional explanations\n- **Verbose language**: Replace procedures with outcomes, multi-step -> single action\n- **Dependency bloat**: Remove redundant/unused dependencies, or stages not referenced in instructions\n---\n**Auto-fix Examples**:\n- Remove: \"npm install\", \"run command\", \"I will now...\", tool tutorials\n- Simplify: \"Click the button and wait\" -> \"Button clicked\", \"Run 'ls' to see files\" -> (Delete)\n- Prefer: Use existing tools (Read/Edit/Grep) over generic bash commands when possible\n\n### Other Issues (use question tool)\n- **Gaps**: Missing prerequisites, incomplete success criteria, undocumented assumptions\n- **Inconsistencies**: Conflicting instructions, mismatched dependencies, naming drift\n- **Bad testing**: Brittle, flaky, redundant, or missing test coverage for critical paths\n- **Assumptions**: Hardcoded values without context, implicit state\n\n### Optimizations (suggest): \n- Parallelizable steps, prefer Read/Edit/Grep over bash\n\n### Test Review Rule\nFor both **plan reviews** and **implementation reviews**, when reviewing tests, test strategy, coverage quality, brittleness, or validation design, use the `quality-engineer` skill.\n\n## Output Format\n- \"Fixed: (Brief changelist of auto-fixes)\"\n- For medium+ issues: Use `question` tool to ask how to proceed\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776157434127},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_E5bVOR1eNqsvZYnZl6Tltj8B|fc_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de02f9fdd4819995a2e96ef9219484","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Spec Review\n\nReview specs for quality, completeness, and feasibility.\n\n## Target Path\n`.agents/tasks/<id>/spec.md`\n\n## Spec-Specific Checks\n- **Clarity**: Is the spec clearly expressed? Is the problem being solved obvious?\n- **Completeness**: Are all necessary details included?\n- **Feasibility**: Is this achievable with reasonable effort?\n- **Missing context**: What information would help refine this?\n- **Missing prerequisites**: Any dependencies or requirements not mentioned?\n- **Scope**: Is the scope appropriate (not too broad/narrow)?\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776157434128},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_LsoD1TQb7KEa4a4POd4wdmu8|fc_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de02f9fde08199921a0a7a161ea740","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MultiCodex Extension - Agent Notes\n\n## Scope\n\nOnly edit files in this directory:\n\n```\n~/.pi/agent/extensions/multicodex/\n```\n\n## Goals\n\n- Keep the extension runnable when installed outside the pi monorepo.\n- Avoid deep imports that resolve to repo-local paths.\n- Keep runtime behavior compatible with pi extension docs.\n\n## Type Safety\n\n- Use public exports from `@mariozechner/pi-ai` and `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent`.\n- The local `pi-coding-agent.d.ts` module augmentation is for TypeScript only and must stay minimal.\n\n## Checks\n\nRun:\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint\nnpm run tsgo\nnpm run test\n```\n\n## Project Management\n- [Tasks](.agents/tasks/task.md)\n- [Log](.agents/log)\n\n## Project Context\n- [Docs](.agents/docs/docs.md)\n- [Sources](.agents/sources/sources.md)\n- [pi-multicodex source code](.agents/sources/pi-multicodex)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776157434128},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_xbGhbEMSuBhYCj146EB9d2le|fc_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de02f9fde48199bd16fbdaa2d58b1f","toolName":"ls","content":[{"type":"text","text":"context/\ncontext.md\nprogress.md\nspec.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776157434128},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Exploring file structure**\n\nI need to check the specifications and any related files. The README, index.ts, and index.test.ts look important too. Maybe I should take a moment to list out the repository structure and file paths to get a clearer view. Having everything organized will definitely help in understanding what’s going on and ensure I’m on the right track. Let’s dive into that!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de0300b1348199840b99ae92075be3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp3gMExdYcfQ9EW_c8L_FwOeq1klx1FrjCybxS_aOQ_Uhj9j-ED0znmJPemfuV41pvdKgVnCz8sAfdtwOFaM0EthHaRFlZQOsmr-hLjpKkwXKwj9I3zn54jMdFgmJqQ1QTJ10o6Xm1nOfuvY2e2LIn588GiqMLbh1LcAE8ujtkOJn4o2TYuv3p8CRRW3blbMTgES0k7jgb6mNM6k7x