**Patching storage and migration behavior**\\n\\nI see that I need to patch the storage and migration behavior to reflect the actual current file path. I should add that the current canonical pi adapter path is /.pi/agent/multicodex.json, with the non-pi path injected. It's essential to support reading the current unversioned file from that path. The `.agents/sources/pi-multicodex` format should be optional, along with removing the term \\\"partially corrupt salvageable,\\\" which seems risky if tests support it. Lastly, I’ll update phase 4 to clarify non-pi validation as a test-only smoke consumer or fixture.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating migration concerns**\\n\\nI'm weighing whether the specifications say that root exports will still function during the migration window. However, it doesn't clarify if the final outcome can retain root as the default extension only. That might be fine, but I should double-check whether `formatResetAt` is included in the module map linked to core/usage.ts, despite it currently only relating to the adapter UI formatting. It’s important to ensure everything's working correctly!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying token management**\\n\\nI'm thinking about token management here. Valid tokens are crucial, but expired tokens need special handling. It's important that when refreshing tokens, I make sure that there's no duplication per account. If multiple callers try to refresh the same token at the same time, it could create issues. Once the refresh is successful, the updated credentials must be securely saved back to managed storage. I want to ensure this process runs smoothly!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Updating core exports**\\n\\nI need to pinpoint the exact section to replace, starting from \\\"### Core exports\\\" and ending just before \\\"### Adapter exports.\\\" It feels like a big task, but I'm up for it. For Patch 4, I need to focus on updating the migration behavior section with a new bullet list. I just want to ensure everything is clear and accurate in the updates I'm making!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_BlHKHSEkpTIEPVE76LIqtWsg|fc_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de04179bc48199aa5be8f990db414a","name":"memex_retro","arguments":{"slug":"spec-parity-contracts-should-exclude-intended-improvements","title":"Parity contracts exclude improvements","body":"When reviewing refactor specs, a behavior-parity section should only capture behavior that exists in the current implementation. If the spec mixes in intended improvements like per-account refresh deduplication, it turns a preservation contract into hidden scope growth and makes acceptance criteria ambiguous. Link this check whenever a spec claims alignment with current code and tests, especially around exported APIs and retry semantics. Related: [[public-api-compatibility-should-match-actual-exports]]","category":"architecture"},"partialJson":"{\"slug\":\"spec-parity-contracts-should-exclude-intended-improvements\",\"title\":\"Parity contracts exclude improvements\",\"body\":\"When reviewing refactor specs, a behavior-parity section should only capture behavior that exists in the current implementation. If the spec mixes in intended improvements like per-account refresh deduplication, it turns a preservation contract into hidden scope growth and makes acceptance criteria ambiguous. Link this check whenever a spec claims alignment with current code and tests, especially around exported APIs and retry semantics. Related: [[public-api-compatibility-should-match-actual-exports]]\",\"category\":\"architecture\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":4364,"output":3437,"cacheRead":40320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48121,"cost":{"input":0.010910000000000001,"output":0.051555000000000004,"cacheRead":0.010079999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.072545}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776157629361,"responseId":"resp_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de03be22f881999a3f02cb59fa6730"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_BlHKHSEkpTIEPVE76LIqtWsg|fc_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de04179bc48199aa5be8f990db414a","toolName":"memex_retro","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Card 'spec-parity-contracts-should-exclude-intended-improvements' saved successfully."}],"details":{},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776157723321},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Documenting patch suggestions**\n\nI need to use code fences and mention the updated progress file. It’s important to point out the current exports from `index.ts` like `StorageData`, `isAccountAvailable`, and others that haven’t been exported. I should also highlight that `formatResetAt` is only used by the status command for UI formatting. I’ll craft clear patch suggestions without line numbers but by referencing section headings, possibly combining suggestions and exact replacements while being thorough.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_04c81ebd48e02dfc0169de041dd95c819995fbc4c0df90091a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp3gQp0fTT9uEHMnRaGV98gDXTQbbwsvq6fIo2GHg2HVyD7zd9ZcortSMv8WbsFPYm7LkN72zwoZjElWWJSNqfOPWMiBhJOlxhZzoib6DZHTEl5xf1g5pW_D0ZXkKOx64BUsPlyZy-XeidLM4QzW-aRxn9EOjG6RKEKuQ922fkURquJ_WiHgzvhvyX6g4vB1GjD872ofNyGO1k1U-vZczEKRe7z-9pNCqWT9OTQNXrc0cUS2AdQxnsf3q6-0SjO0Up7Snl6pF_EwNsM4HR3_khmipWvhLIx1Nd9ao--anAuqjIHLmulKr6fP7lrLIcEvkEcRUKW82xp5DbNnCn-JAxvPgcba--JBBkNNupXntdUeAXUey_sUkiKe-iXqt6JHL8Vv7_GcwC0uLRNxT8-ADQtMMz-LvIEqUwsaICcCET1wzYne883hqGnjbOFlPImS6zotSz_ToKnkJB1VGcHRRSYuHojXoO4teKmbLfKHoFVqjT4y-czSZii0Q7z1iMk2GT3N-TX7j5IwMBrjXb0X_YRjiOhCWZK6QYCHEu9syctcUxdBW1eGw_ZFgST1fX5DhQUqokkdU6oYidfZ7s6eDdvr5twrtUEij1yopk-98f4gN5mqjwa2GD2J70YoobzE2B4Xg40eAEGEkPWr6AyaJXxisVVfYzwkfVXDSGkhSnpTqVcUmcBuZfNBJu9Luzfwwpt7ylC41ZUTBJfKLIAsEvd8BviRBRGSl_ZFWRh7NgogazvyMHuzIwvd4ltb1kToNAscaS8xWpamWxVmq-vyAfkxp1FwxJ3c7fKsiSpKtqi58QJGuE5c7TECOTTO5p1KWZgEYWEOtmSN_3zEt1fX6UHgJTE5ZLNORDOMoLdxJ-Q0T3fGdN4YVQh6eNZCH13hRepbjNGZCm5UmOMKfIx2is7D